1. Definitions

   "Software" means the Deployer source code, container images built from it,
   documentation, JSON templates, MCP tools and resources, and other files in
   this repository, including modifications you make.

   "End Users" means third parties who use your products or services.

   "Your Product" means applications, content, or services that you own or have
   the right to offer, where the primary value to End Users is not access to
   deployment-management capabilities provided by the Software.

   "Competing Offering" means a product or service whose primary purpose is
   multi-tenant or template-based container deployment, container lifecycle
   management, volume orchestration across hosts, or AI/agent-driven Docker
   deployment administration (including via MCP or similar protocols), whether
   offered for a fee or at no charge.

